    "Furthermore, to investigate the effect of size on the performance of the pre-trained model using MURA, DenseNet-161 was trained in subsets of the lower extremity dataset of different sizes (1,000, 5,000, 10,000, and 50,000).",
    "The results showed that for small training datasets, pretraining in MURA significantly increased performance (AUC-ROC risen from 0.67 to 0.78 for the subset of 1000).",
    "The study findings suggested that TL presents a promising strategy for improving the model performance for the abnormality detection task when the labelled training dataset is limited.",
